olutions please read.</span><hr size=1>  <br>
 I came up with some things I would like you to think about and talk with the other team leads about. I think these two ideas would help with some problems at hand.<br>
 <br>
 1) In the assassin realm of classes, two of the 3 are not broken. Once &quot;re-spec&quot; is put in, Shadowblades will be able to change their templates around to their style of play and infiltrators are fine as is. This leaves Nightshade as the assassin class that needs just a little bump to fall in line with the other 2.<br>
 -problem.. Nightshades are lacking in the ability to last long enough in a fight to do the damage that the other two assassin classes can. This is mainly due to race restrictions that leave them with low constitution and low hit points.<br>
 -Solution.. By design Nightshades are suppose to be weak. The realm abilities give some leeway but not enough to bring them in line with their counterparts in the other two realms who also get realm abilities. As a hybrid caster, Nightshades should receive the &quot;ABSORB&quot; buff of 5% that all Direct damage pure casters get (pure casters also get a 10% absorb buff, but this is to much for shades). This buff will allow them to last a little longer in melee situations while not covering their weakness of low hit points and constitution. It is also in Line with the caster part of the class.<br>
 <br>
 2) Recently character moves to &quot;Pendragon&quot; and &quot;Mordred&quot; were automated for the public. A problem on many servers is the balance of realm vs realm in the RVR high end game. Through the use of character transfer automation some resolution can be accomplished.<br>
 -Problem.. Some servers lack enough players in the enemy realm at high enough levels to make RvR fun. Often times large groups on one side have no counter from the other realms and soon those players become bored with the content and DAoC in general.<br>
 -Solution.. Allow characters to log on to a server of their choice and make a level 1 character reserving the name and complete the character &quot;copy&quot; as was done for the &quot;Pendragon&quot; test. But set a limit to transfers for each server based on RP status earned by the realms in the past 7 days. If your realm is earning the most RP on your server for the past 7 days, no transfers to your realm can be made. A reply is sent through e-mail informing you that the move to that server will not be processed due to realm vs realm balance issues.<br>
 <br>
 With item #2 above I can see a lot of people saying that if you limit who can be on a server in a certain realm, then friends can not join and new players would be forced onto servers they don't want to be on. This is not true. This will not effect new players or the making of characters on a server at all. What it will do is keep established strong rvr realms from getting stronger while allowing some of the strong rvr players from other servers to copy over within their realm and boost their side of the war between the realms on the server with the balance problem. <br>
 <br>
 It will also allow people to move to servers where they will have the most fun and find a home where they are happy with DAoC and making new friends. Adding a new dimension to the RvR aspect of the game.<br>
 <br>
 Think on this for a bit.. (exactly how I worded it, not reading to much into it) and see what you think.<br>
 <br>
 Take care!<br>
